#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.213"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.213:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.213:0.2"
msgid "22. Akkosakavagga "
msgstr "22. Abuse "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.213:0.3"
msgid "213. Sīlasutta "
msgstr "213. Ethics "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.213:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks for an unethical person because of their failure in ethics. "

msgctxt "an5.213:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.213:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno pamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahatiṃ bhogajāniṃ nigacchati. "
msgstr "Firstly, an unethical person loses substantial wealth on account of negligence. "

msgctxt "an5.213:1.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the first drawback. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.213:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlassa sīlavipannassa pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person gets a bad reputation. "

msgctxt "an5.213:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the second drawback. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.253, sc3
msgctxt "an5.213:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ, yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ, yadi gahapatiparisaṃ, yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—avisārado upasaṅkamati maṅkubhūto. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person enters any kind of assembly timid and embarrassed, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics. "

msgctxt "an5.213:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the third drawback. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.213:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person dies feeling lost. "

msgctxt "an5.213:4.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the fourth drawback. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.213:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dussīlo sīlavipanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person, when their body breaks up, after death, is reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "an5.213:5.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the fifth drawback. "

msgctxt "an5.213:5.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā. "
msgstr "These are the five drawbacks for an unethical person because of their failure in ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an5.213:6.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāya. "
msgstr "There are these five benefits for an ethical person because of their accomplishment in ethics. "

msgctxt "an5.213:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.213:6.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno appamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahantaṃ bhogakkhandhaṃ adhigacchati. "
msgstr "Firstly, an ethical person gains substantial wealth on account of diligence. "

msgctxt "an5.213:6.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya. "
msgstr "This is the first benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an5.213:7.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavato sīlasampannassa kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person gets a good reputation. "

msgctxt "an5.213:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya. "
msgstr "This is the second benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an5.213:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—yadi khattiyaparisaṃ, yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ, yadi gahapatiparisaṃ, yadi samaṇaparisaṃ—visārado upasaṅkamati amaṅkubhūto. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person enters any kind of assembly bold and self-assured, whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics. "

msgctxt "an5.213:8.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ bhikkhave, tatiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya. "
msgstr "This is the third benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an5.213:9.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person dies not feeling lost. "

msgctxt "an5.213:9.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya. "
msgstr "This is the fourth benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.254, sc10
msgctxt "an5.213:10.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, sīlavā sīlasampanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, when an ethical person’s body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "an5.213:10.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya. "
msgstr "This is the fifth benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.213:10.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāyā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the five benefits for an ethical person because of their accomplishment in ethics.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.213:10.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

